#compdef elm-language-server
# =============================================================================
# elm-language-server — elm-tooling organization's
#                       "Implementation of an elm language
#                       server in node" — the official
#                       Language Server Protocol (LSP)
#                       implementation for the Elm
#                       programming language.  Provides
#                       IDE-level features (autocompletion,
#                       hover documentation, go-to-
#                       definition, find-references,
#                       rename, code actions, diagnostics)
#                       to any LSP-compatible editor: VS
#                       Code, Neovim, Emacs, Helix, Sublime
#                       Text, Atom, JetBrains IDEs, etc.
#                       Written in TypeScript, runs on
#                       Node.js, distributed via npm.
#                       Distinguishing from the official
#                       elm compiler's diagnostic-only
#                       output, the elm-test reporter,
#                       and various community Elm IDE
#                       plugins by:
#                         - WEB-TREE-SITTER PARSING — uses
#                           the WebAssembly build of
#                           tree-sitter (web-tree-sitter)
#                           loaded into Node.js to parse
#                           Elm source files into ASTs,
#                           enabling semantic analysis,
#                           symbol indexing, and AST-
#                           aware refactoring operations
#                           (this is the headline CLI
#                           library that closes Axis 31
#                           on the TS-Node side; see
#                           taxonomy notes below)
#                         - @ELM-TOOLING/TREE-SITTER-ELM
#                           — Kolja Lampe's tree-sitter
#                           grammar for Elm, maintained
#                           alongside elm-language-server;
#                           handles Elm's significant-
#                           whitespace + record-type +
#                           pattern-match + custom-type
#                           syntax
#                         - VSCODE-LANGUAGESERVER —
#                           uses Microsoft's vscode-
#                           languageserver/node package
#                           as the LSP framework; handles
#                           the JSON-RPC protocol layer +
#                           transport (stdio, socket,
#                           node-ipc, pipe)
#                         - CHOKIDAR FILE WATCHING — uses
#                           paulmillr/chokidar (Axis 17
#                           covered) to watch the project
#                           directory + reparse modified
#                           files
#                         - TSYRINGE DEPENDENCY INJECTION
#                           — uses Microsoft's tsyringe
#                           lightweight DI container to
#                           wire LSP service classes
#                         - EXECA SUBPROCESS — uses
#                           sindresorhus/execa to invoke
#                           the upstream `elm` compiler
#                           for type-checking + diagnostic
#                           generation; LSP merges these
#                           with tree-sitter-derived
#                           syntactic diagnostics
#                         - ELM-FORMAT INTEGRATION —
#                           shells out to `elm-format` for
#                           format-on-save behavior
#                         - ELM-REVIEW + ELM-TEST AWARE
#                           — recognizes elm-review +
#                           elm-test conventions to
#                           surface lint warnings +
#                           test status in editor
#                           diagnostics
#                         - FAST-DIFF FOR INCREMENTAL
#                           EDITS — uses jhildenbiddle/
#                           fast-diff for character-level
#                           diffing of document changes,
#                           enabling fine-grained tree-
#                           sitter incremental re-parsing
#                         - TRANSPORT FLEXIBILITY — LSP
#                           supports stdio (default),
#                           socket (TCP), node-ipc, pipe
#                           (named pipe) transports; the
#                           server detects which via
#                           command-line arguments
#                         - CANCELLATION TOKENS — supports
#                           LSP's cancellation protocol
#                           via --cancellationReceive +
#                           --cancellationSend arguments
#                           (file-based cancellation
#                           between client and server)
#                         - ZERO-CONFIG — works without
#                           any configuration for a
#                           standard `elm.json`-based
#                           project; advanced users can
#                           pass capability hints via the
#                           initialize() LSP request
#                       Used by: every Elm developer using
#                       an LSP-capable editor (VS Code's
#                       elmLS extension, Neovim's coc-
#                       elm + native LSP clients, Helix,
#                       Emacs's lsp-mode + eglot, Sublime
#                       LSP), and as the reference Elm
#                       LSP implementation since the
#                       deprecation of the official
#                       Elm-package-manager-bundled IDE
#                       integration.
#
# Author:  Kolja Lampe (razzeee) + elm-tooling
#          organization maintainers.  License: MIT.
#          Active development with continuous releases.
# Source:  https://github.com/elm-tooling/elm-language-server
#          https://github.com/elm-tooling/elm-language-server/blob/master/src/node/index.ts
#          https://github.com/elm-tooling/elm-language-server/blob/master/src/common.ts
# Manpage: No traditional manpage; documentation in repo
#          README.md + LSP spec at https://microsoft.github
#          .io/language-server-protocol/.
# Library: web-tree-sitter (WebAssembly tree-sitter — the
#          headline dependency for this completion's
#          axis-closing role; see taxonomy notes below).
#          Also vscode-languageserver (Microsoft's LSP
#          framework), chokidar (Axis 17 file watching),
#          execa (subprocess), tsyringe (DI), reflect-
#          metadata, fast-diff (diff algorithm), globby
#          (glob), request-light (HTTP), @elm-tooling/
#          tree-sitter-elm (the Elm grammar package).
# License: MIT
